T1  - Nonparametric Identification and Estimation of Nonadditive Hedonic Models
AU  - Heckman, James J.
AU  - Matzkin, Rosa L.
AU  - Nesheim, Lars
Y1  - 2010/09/01
PY  - 2010
DA  - 2010/09/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA6388
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 1569
EP  - 1591
VL  - 78
IS  - 5
KW  - Hedonic models
KW  - hedonic equilibrium
KW  - nonadditive models
KW  - identification
KW  - nonparametric estimation
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA6388
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - This paper studies the identification and estimation of preferences and technologies in equilibrium hedonic models. In it, we identify nonparametric structural relationships with nonadditive heterogeneity. We determine what features of hedonic models can be identified from equilibrium observations in a single market under weak assumptions about the available information. We then consider use of additional information about structural functions and heterogeneity distributions. Separability conditions facilitate identification of consumer marginal utility and firm marginal product functions. We also consider how identification is facilitated using multimarket data.
ER  - 

